page.title: 03PLACE-NAMES
page.content: If you were to take a look at a map of this area, you would see several strange looking names. Most names in this area are derived from the Norse language used by the Vikings during their occupation: {MYRE}_soft,soggy ground. {WARSETTER}_War being derived from the Norse "Varthi"meaning watchtower and setter,also Norse,meaning hill pasture. {STOVE}_coming from norse word "stofa"meaning room. {SKEDGABIST}_"skedge" is likely to be a Norse earl or god,and "Bist"is Norse meaning dwelling. {HOWAR}_Norse word meaning high ground. {NEBISTERS}_"Bister" again meaning dwelling."Ne" means near. {POOL}_area of land covered by sea at high tide.
